  "local_port": 47552,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I recover a Yahoo hacked email address?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that your Yahoo email account has been compromised. Recovering a hacked Yahoo email account involves several steps to secure your account and regain access. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you through the process:\n\n### 1. **Attempt to Sign In to Your Account**\n\n- **Go to the Yahoo Sign-In Page:** Visit [login.yahoo.com](https://login.yahoo.com/).\n- **Enter Your Credentials:** Input your Yahoo email address and password.\n- **If You Can Access Your Account:**\n  - **Change Your Password Immediately:** Go to [Account Security](https://login.yahoo.com/account/security) and update your password to a strong, unique one.\n  - **Review Recent Activity:** Check for any unauthorized activity or changes to your account settings.\n  - **Update Recovery Information:** Ensure your recovery email address and phone number are correct.\n  - **Enable Two-Step Verification:** This adds an extra layer of security. You can enable it [here](https://login.yahoo.com/account/security).\n\n### 2. **If You Can't Access Your Account**\n\nIf you're unable to sign in because the hacker changed your password or recovery information, follow these steps:\n\n#### **a. Go to Yahoo's Account Recovery Page**\n\n- **Visit the Recovery Page:** Navigate to [Yahoo Account Recovery](https://login.yahoo.com/forgot).\n\n#### **b. Provide Your Email Address**\n\n- **Enter Your Yahoo Email:** Input the email address you\u2019re trying to recover and click \"Continue.\"\n\n#### **c. Verify Your Identity**\n\nYahoo will offer several options to verify your identity, depending on the recovery information you provided earlier:\n\n- **Recovery Email Address:** Yahoo will send a verification code to your recovery email. Access that email to retrieve the code.\n- **Mobile Phone Number:** Yahoo can send a verification code via SMS to your linked phone number.\n- **Alternative Methods:** If you don't have access to the above, you might need to answer security questions or provide other verification details.\n\n#### **d. Reset Your Password**\n\n- **Enter the Verification Code:** Input the code you received to proceed.\n- **Create a New Password:** Choose a strong password that you haven't used before on this account. A combination of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols is recommended.\n\n### 3. **If You're Unable to Recover Your Account Online**\n\nIf the standard recovery methods don't work, you may need to contact Yahoo Support directly:\n\n- **Visit the Yahoo Help Center:** Go to [Yahoo Help](https://help.yahoo.com/kb/account).\n- **Explore the Recovery Options:** Look for topics related to account recovery or security breaches.\n- **Contact Support:** Depending on your region, you might find options to email, chat, or call Yahoo customer support for further assistance.\n\n### 4. **After Regaining Access: Secure Your Account**\n\nOnce you've recovered your account, take these steps to secure it and prevent future unauthorized access:\n\n- **Update Your Password:** Ensure it's strong and unique.\n- **Review Account Information:** Check your recovery email, phone number, and other personal information for any unauthorized changes.\n- **Check Account Activity:** Look for any unfamiliar devices or locations that have accessed your account.\n- **Remove Suspicious Apps or Extensions:** Revoke access to any third-party apps you don't recognize.\n- **Enable Two-Step Verification:** This adds an extra security layer by requiring a second form of verification when logging in.\n- **Monitor Your Account Regularly:** Keep an eye on your account activity and be cautious of phishing attempts.\n\n### 5. **Prevent Future Hacks**\n\n- **Use a Strong, Unique Password:** Avoid using the same password across multiple sites.\n- **Be Cautious with Emails and Links:** Don't click on suspicious links or provide personal information to unverified sources.\n- **Keep Software Updated:** Ensure your devices have the latest security updates and antivirus software.\n- **Educate Yourself on Phishing Scams:** Learn how to recognize and avoid common phishing tactics.\n\n### 6. **Additional Resources**\n\n- **Yahoo Help Articles:**\n  - [Recover a Hacked Yahoo Account](https://help.yahoo.com/kb/SLN4904.html)\n  - [Yahoo Account Security Tips](https://help.yahoo.com/kb/SLN23967.html)\n- **Yahoo Customer Support:** Access through the [Yahoo Help Center](https://help.yahoo.com/).\n\n### 7. **Consider Legal Action if Necessary**\n\nIf you believe your account was hacked as part of a larger criminal activity, you might want to report it to your local law enforcement agency.\n\n---\n\n**Important Tips:**\n\n- **Act Quickly:** The sooner you attempt to recover your account, the better chance you have of minimizing damage.\n- **Avoid Using Public Wi-Fi for Recovery:** Use a secure and private internet connection to access your account during the recovery process.\n- **Backup Important Data:** Once you regain access, consider backing up important emails and contacts.\n\nBy following these steps diligently, you should be able to recover your hacked Yahoo email account and secure it against future unauthorized access.",
